---
const rows = [
  {
    operation: "Schnorr P2TR verify",
    time: "~27 \u00B5s",
    ratio: "1\u00D7",
    bar: 1.5,
  },
  {
    operation: "SPHINCS+ verify",
    time: "~1,756 \u00B5s",
    ratio: "64\u00D7",
    bar: 64,
  },
  {
    operation: "SPHINCS+ sign",
    time: "~918 ms",
    ratio: "33,600\u00D7",
    bar: 100,
  },
];
---

<section id="benchmarks" class="border-t border-border py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-6">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight md:text-4xl">
        Performance
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-text-secondary">
        SPHINCS+ verification is ~64x slower than Schnorr, reflected in the weighted
        sigop cost. Signing is offline and doesn't affect block validation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6">
      {rows.map((row) => (
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-raised p-5">
          <div class="mb-3 flex items-baseline justify-between">
            <span class="font-medium">{row.operation}</span>
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3">
              <span class="font-mono text-sm text-text-secondary">{row.time}</span>
              <span class="rounded bg-surface-overlay px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-quantum">
                {row.ratio}
              </span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="h-2 overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-surface-overlay">
            <div
              class="h-full rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-quantum to-btc-orange"
              style={`width: ${row.bar}%`}
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-raised p-6 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary text-center">
        <span class="font-mono text-text-primary">VALIDATION_WEIGHT_PER_SPHINCS_SIGOP = 3200</span>
        <br />
        64&times; Schnorr&rsquo;s weight of 50 &mdash; ensures SPHINCS+ transactions
        pay proportional block-space cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h3 class="mb-4 text-lg font-semibold text-center">Test Coverage</h3>
      <div class="grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-raised p-4 text-center">
          <div class="mb-1 font-mono text-xl font-bold text-quantum">56</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-secondary">Consensus tests<br/>(BIP 368 + 369)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-raised p-4 text-center">
          <div class="mb-1 font-mono text-xl font-bold text-btc-orange">75</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-secondary">Wallet unit tests<br/>(key, qextkey, descriptor, DB)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-border bg-surface-raised p-4 text-center">
          <div class="mb-1 font-mono text-xl font-bold text-text-primary">37</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-secondary">Wallet functional tests<br/>(RPCs, PSBT, activation)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
